            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="my-3">Overview</h3>
                <p>Sandy's Compound is a 30-year-old sports complex located in Bhagalpur City, Bihar, opposite the police line in Bhagalpur. It is a multifaceted recreational area that includes various sports facilities and a charming natural setting, making it one of the best fields in Bhagalpur.</p>
                <h3 class="my-3">History</h3>
                <p>The land for Sandy's Compound was acquired by the government in 1906 for public purposes. It was named after a Briton who served as the Mayor of Bhagalpur at the time. The acquisition of this piece of land, which measures approximately 307 bighas, 15 cottahs, and 14 chitaks, was documented in the Calcutta Gazette on July 18, 1906.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="my-3">Sports Facilities</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Doordarshan TV Centre:</b> Located within the compound, this center serves as a significant media hub in the region.</li>
                    <li><b>Volleyball Court:</b> A well-maintained court for volleyball enthusiasts.</li>
                    <li><b>Small Open Stadium:</b> Suitable for hosting various sports events and activities.</li>
                    <li><b>State Level Matches:</b> The complex hosts state-level matches, making it a crucial venue for sports in Bhagalpur.</li>
                    <li><b>Tennis and Basketball Courts:</b> State-of-the-art facilities for tennis and basketball players.</li>
                    <li><b>Cricket Stadium:</b> Although small, this stadium has historical significance as it hosted a Ranji Trophy match in 1981/82 where the Bihar cricket team defeated the Assam cricket team by an innings and 2 runs.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

